How many libraries do you use?  Are you sure they don&#x27;t create their own threads?<p>Also, just imagine something like this:<p><pre><code>    file.write(blah);
    if (has_forked) thread_exit();
    file.write(blah2);
    if (has_forked) thread_exit();
    file.write(blah3)
    if (has_forked) thread_exit();
</code></pre>
Note the race conditions in the above code... forkall() is a disaster.  Presumably you&#x27;d combine it with pthread_atfork(), but it&#x27;s still a total mess.
